[The date given by the manuscript is confirmed by the mention of Zasius' book (cf. Ep. 376. 10 n.) and of the two sons-in-law, the second of whom had married Zasius’ younger daughter in 1515 (cf. Ep. 357. 14 n.). The letter is clearly written to Basle, and thus 1516 is the only year possible out os those covered by the Deventer Letter-book (App. 8).

In the manuscript the remainder of the page after the letter is filled up by In Nouum Testamentum ab Erasmo Ro. translatum hexastich0n3 to which Leclerc prefixes the name of Zasius. The attribution is probably correct, and thus supplies confirmation for the date of the letter ; but it has no authority.]
